A RESOLUTION
1 Creating and authorizing the House Special Committee on Oversight of Federal Funds; to
2 provide for the issuance of compulsory process to secure the attendance of witnesses or the
3 production of documents and materials; and for other purposes.
4 WHEREAS, the use of federal funds as well as compliance with federally required auditing
5 procedures merits close scrutiny and oversight; and
6 WHEREAS, it is important to collect information from other branches of government,
7 including subpoena and compelled testimony, relating to the use of federal funds and
8 auditing procedures; and
9 WHEREAS, a complete list of all federal funds received by the state, including the amount,
10 purpose, source, recipients of such funds, criteria for distribution of such funds, and funds
11 not expended and the reasons why, should be compiled and should include:
12 (1) A copy of the initial Notice of Grant Award from the federal government to this state
13 for the prior three years;
14 (2) A list of accounts and project ledger names for the recording of expenditures by project
15 detail, the identity of the accounting system used to track costs, and a list of reports used
16 to track costs by project;
