17 (3) The most recent copy of financial statements, balance sheet of funds, income received
18 for funds, and any and all balance sheets related to funds; and
19 (4) Budget comparisons with actual expenditures on a monthly basis precluding drawdown
20 of federal funds in excess of total funds authorized on the Notice of Grant Award, total
21 funds available for any cost category, either restricted or nonrestricted, on the Notice of
22 Grant Award; and
23 WHEREAS, reports on the progress of programs funded with federal dollars, including
24 performance data and outcome measures, should be issued on a regular basis, to include:
25 (1) A listing of accounting entries with evidence to support the entry. A listing of
26 personnel and their responsibilities for receipt, payment, distribution, and recording of
27 federal funds;
28 (2) A listing of all established tracking expenditure policies and procedures against budget
29 or the funding amounts. If tracked, provide documentation to suffice for the monitoring
30 of tracked funds received and distributed; and
31 (3) A list of personnel responsible for tracking and monitoring federal funds and projects,
32 including dollar amounts; and
33 WHEREAS, a complete list of all relevant federal guidelines, regulations, and funding
34 agreements, as well as any waivers or exemptions granted from federal requirements, would
35 be of great value; and
36 WHEREAS, information on any audits or evaluations conducted on the use of federal funds,
37 including findings and recommendations, and information on any instances of misuse or
38 misappropriation of federal funds, including any investigations and corrective actions taken,
39 should be made available; and
