63 WHEREAS, Article III, Section IV, Paragraph IV of the Georgia Constitution provides for
64 the creation of interim committees pursuant to the authority of the General Assembly or of
65 either house.
66 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES:
67 (1) Delegation of authority and creation and authorization of the house special
68 committee. The House of Representatives hereby delegates its powers to the House
69 Special Committee on Oversight of Federal Funds, which is created and authorized.
70 (2) Members and officers. The committee shall be composed of nine members to be
71 appointed as follows:
72 (A) A chairperson who shall be a member of the House of Representatives appointed
73 by the Speaker of the House of Representatives;
74 (B) Four members of the House of Representatives appointed by the House Majority
75 Leader; and
76 (C) Four members of the House of Representatives appointed by the House Minority
77 Leader.
78 (3) Powers and duties. The committee is hereby authorized to undertake a legislative
79 investigation into the issues mentioned above or related thereto. For the purpose of
80 conducting any investigation as provided herein, the committee shall have the power to
81 administer oaths; to call any party to testify under oath at such investigations; to require
82 the attendance of witnesses and the production of books, records, and papers; and to take
83 the depositions of witnesses. For such purposes, the committee is authorized to issue
84 subpoenas for any witness or to compel the production of any books, records, or papers
85 and is further authorized to undertake such actions as may be necessary to enforce such
86 subpoenas in cases of refusal to obey. The committee may establish rules of operation;
87 provided, however, the committee may not establish rules that authorize one member to
88 issue subpoenas without the consent of the committee as demonstrated by a majority vote
