89 at a meeting where a quorum is present or without the express, written consent of the
90 chairperson of the committee.
91 (4) Meetings. The chairperson shall call all meetings of the committee. The committee
92 may conduct such meetings at such places and at such times as it may deem necessary or
93 convenient, including at any time during the interim period occurring following the
94 House of Representatives adjourning sine die, to enable it to exercise fully and effectively
95 its powers, perform its duties, and accomplish the objectives and purposes of this
96 resolution.
97 (5) Allowances and Funding.
98 (A) The legislative members of the committee shall receive the allowances provided
99 for in Code Section 28-1-8 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated.
100 (B) The allowances authorized by this resolution shall not be received by any member
101 of the committee for more than five days unless additional days are authorized. Funds
102 necessary to carry out the provisions of this resolution shall come from funds
103 appropriated to the House of Representatives.
104 (6) Report.
105 (A) In the event the committee adopts any specific findings or recommendations that
106 include suggestions for proposed legislation or changes in appropriations, the
107 chairperson shall file a report of the same, subject to subparagraph (C) of this
108 paragraph.
109 (B) In the event the committee adopts a report that does not include suggestions for
110 proposed legislation or changes in appropriations, the chairperson shall file the report,
111 subject to subparagraph (C) of this paragraph.
112 (C) No report shall be filed unless the same has been approved by majority vote of a
113 quorum of the committee. A report so approved shall be signed by the chairperson of
114 the committee and filed with the Clerk of the House of Representatives.
